value.value: A rare, benign wart-like skin lesion of unknown etiology that is usually found in the genital or perianal area and consists of hyperkeratosis and aggregates of foam cell macrophages.
A peripheral nervous system neoplasm that arises from the dermis.
A class of agents that increases the production of urine by the kidney. Via various mechanism of actions, diuretics retain water in urine, thus provides a means of forced diuresis.
A smooth muscle neoplasm occurring in the skin.
A ganglioneuroma arising from the skin.
